# Fix: Link Button Not Working

## Context

The link toolbar button (and floating toolbar link button) silently fail. Root cause: when creating a new link, the Toolbar dispatches `TOGGLE_LINK_COMMAND` with payload `'https://'`. The `LinkPlugin` handler calls `validateUrl('https://')`, which runs `new URL('https://')` — this **throws** because `https://` alone is not a valid URL (no hostname). So `validateUrl` returns `false`, the handler returns `false`, and the link is never created.

Same issue exists in `FloatingSelectionToolbar.jsx` which also dispatches `TOGGLE_LINK_COMMAND` with `'https://'`.

## Root Cause

**File:** `Toolbar.jsx:379` and `FloatingSelectionToolbar.jsx:103`
```js
editor.dispatchCommand(TOGGLE_LINK_COMMAND, 'https://');
// ↑ LinkPlugin calls validateUrl('https://') → new URL('https://') → THROWS → returns false
```

**File:** `RichTextEditor.jsx:290`, `ChapterEditor.jsx:204`, `editJournal.jsx`
```jsx
<LinkPlugin validateUrl={(url) => {
    try { return Boolean(new URL(url)); } catch { return false; }
}} />
// ↑ 'https://' has no hostname, so new URL() throws, returns false
```

## Fix

Two-part fix — both are needed:

### 1. Toolbar.jsx (line ~379) — Use `$toggleLink` directly instead of dispatching command with placeholder URL

Replace the `toggleLink` function to call `$toggleLink` inside `editor.update()` which bypasses the `validateUrl` check for the initial creation. The FloatingLinkEditor will handle actual URL editing.

```js
const toggleLink = () => {
    editor.update(() => {
        const selection = $getSelection();
        if (!$isRangeSelection(selection)) return;
        if (activeStates.isLink) {
            $toggleLink(null);          // remove link
        } else {
            $toggleLink('https://');    // create link with placeholder
        }
    });
};
```

Requires adding import: `$toggleLink` from `@lexical/link`

### 2. FloatingSelectionToolbar.jsx (line ~103) — Same fix

Replace:
```js
editor.dispatchCommand(TOGGLE_LINK_COMMAND, 'https://');
```
With direct `editor.update()` + `$toggleLink('https://')` call.

Requires adding import: `$toggleLink` from `@lexical/link`

### Files to modify
| File | Change |
|---|---|
| `client/src/components/HomePage/Editor/Toolbar.jsx` | Import `$toggleLink`, rewrite `toggleLink()` to use `editor.update()` |
| `client/src/components/HomePage/Editor/plugins/FloatingSelectionToolbar.jsx` | Import `$toggleLink`, rewrite `toggleLink()` to use `editor.update()` |

## Verification
1. Open editor, select text, click link button → link should be created with `https://` placeholder
2. FloatingLinkEditor should appear showing the URL for editing
3. Click link button again on linked text → link should be removed
4. Select text in floating selection toolbar, click link → same behavior
5. Verify auto-link still works (type a full URL like `https://google.com` → auto-linked)

